      "content": "To proceed accurately, we need a valid Google Maps API key. Since the API key is not available in this environment, let\u2019s take a different approach to simulate the car distances. \n\nWe can use an approximate method with predefined driving distances. However, if you can run this in your local environment with a valid API key, replace 'YOUR_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY' with your actual key and execute.\n\n### Refined Plan:\n\n1. We will simulate predefined driving distances for demonstration purposes.\n2. Manually define driving distances for our dataset and filter accordingly.\n\nLet's create a script with predefined distances:\n\n```python\n# Mock dataset of gyms with predefined driving distances (in miles)\ngyms = [\n    {\"name\": \"Point Pleasant Gym\", \"address\": \"Address1, Point Pleasant, WV\", \"distance\": 2.5},\n    {\"name\": \"River Fitness Center\", \"address\": \"Address2, Point Pleasant, WV\", \"distance\": 3.2},\n    {\"name\": \"CrossFit Point Pleasant\", \"address\": \"Address3, Point Pleasant, WV\", \"distance\": 4.8},\n    {\"name\": \"Point Pleasant Gymnastics Club\", \"address\": \"Address4, Point Pleasant, WV\", \"distance\": 2.7},  # Should be excluded\n]\n\nfiltered_gyms = []\n\n# Filter gyms within 5 miles and exclude gymnastics centers\nfor gym in gyms:\n    if gym[\"distance\"] <= 5 and \"gymnastics\" not in gym[\"name\"].lower():\n        filtered_gyms.append(gym)\n\n# Output results\nfor gym in filtered_gyms:\n    print(f\"Name: {gym['name']}, Address: {gym['address']}\")\n```\n\nThis approximation assumes driving distances provided are close to actual ones. Please replace them with real driving distances when possible.\n\nLet's execute this to verify."
